title: Grateful Dead Live at Cumberland County Civic Center on 1982-09-17
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Promised Land, Candyman-> CC Rider, Althea, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Dupree's Diamond Blues, It's All Over Now, West L.A. Fadeaway, Throwing Stones, Deal

Set 2

Touch Of Gray-> Women Are Smarter, High Time, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> The Other One-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Morning Dew-> Sugar Magnolia, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Guess I'm Not A Purist And thankful.

A Buddy Once Told Me That this was one of his favorite shows and I endeavored to hear it should a full version of it ever turn up on the Archives, 'cuz he had impeccable taste and I sensed hence that I would not be disappointed. Now here, voila!, a full version of this show!

He attended and raved about it. In time he sent me a version that features merely the second set. Well, this is not within my practice. When I listen to a show on this website I listen to it all the way through. The purists stay away from first sets. Guess I'm not a purist.

Whatever that means...

Great show start to finish. Lots of interesting stuff. All good versions. Sweet AUD.

My buddy was right.

This one you can download, place upon your favorite playback medium and enjoy numerous times.
- I think they were in a silly mood this night. Weir sounds like he's making fun of himself way...more than usual. Tentative renditions of "new" songs...whatever...
